cs.WEB, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper focuses on improving the performance of mobile Web applications by reducing redundant data transfers, which is a common issue in the field of Web development. Therefore, cs.WEB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a mechanism for resource packaging and management, which involves efficient storage and retrieval of data, suggesting relevance to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed approach in existing mobile Web architectures, indicating relevance to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
